        <h2>Getting to Anuradhapura</h2>
        <p>Anuradhapura is 5 hours from Colombo by train (the Yal Devi or Uttara Devi express) or 4.5 hours by bus. From Sigiriya, it is about 1.5 hours by car. From Jaffna, it is 3 hours south. The town has a main bus stand and railway station. Within the archaeological zone — which covers a large area — a tuk-tuk is essential for getting between sites efficiently. Negotiate a half-day rate (around LKR 1,500–2,500) to cover the main loop.</p>

        <h2>Tips & Practical Information</h2>
        <p>Remove shoes at all sacred sites. Dress conservatively — cover shoulders and knees. Photography is generally permitted but avoid photographing devotees in prayer. The entry ticket (around USD 25) covers the main archaeological zone — buy at the ticket office near the museum. The best time to visit is early morning (7am) when the light is beautiful and the temperature manageable. Anuradhapura can be done as a day trip from Sigiriya or Habarana but two days allows a more relaxed exploration including Mihintale.</p>
